-- Executive Dashboard Design & Development --

Dashboard Structure

The report will contain 5 pages.

Page 1 — Executive Overview
Audience:
CEO
CFO
COO
KPI Cards
Total Sales
Total Profit
Profit Margin %
Total Orders
Total Customers
Average Order Value
YoY Growth %
MoM Growth %
Visuals
Monthly Sales Trend (Line Chart)
Sales by Category (Column Chart)
Sales by Region (Map or Bar Chart)
Top 10 Products (Bar Chart)
Slicers
Year
Quarter
Region
Category

Page 2 — Sales Performance
Audience:
Sales Director
Regional Managers
Visuals
Sales by State
Sales by City
Sales by Segment
Monthly Sales
Quarterly Sales
Top Customers
Top Sales Representatives (if available in dataset)

Page 3 — Customer Insights
Audience:
Marketing
Customer Success
Sales
KPI Cards
Total Customers
Average Customer Spend
Repeat Customers (if available)
Visuals
Customer Segments
Top Customers
Customer Revenue Contribution
Orders by Segment

Page 4 — Product Performance
Audience:
Product Manager
Merchandising
Operations
Visuals
Sales by Category
Sales by Sub-Category
Top Products
Lowest Profit Products
Quantity Sold
Profit Margin by Category

Page 5 — Regional Performance
Audience:
COO
Regional Sales Managers
Visuals
Filled Map
Regional Sales
Regional Profit
State Performance
City Performance
Profit Margin by Region

Navigation
Each page should include:
Home button
Previous page
Next page
Reset Filters button
Page navigation menu

Theme
Colors
Primary: Dark Blue
Secondary: Light Blue
Positive: Green
Negative: Red
Neutral: Gray
Use the same palette consistently across all pages.

Typography
Font: Segoe UI (or equivalent)
Titles: 18–22 pt
KPI Values: 28–36 pt
Labels: 10–12 pt

Dashboard Design Principles
Every visual must answer one business question.
Avoid:
3D charts
Pie charts with many categories
Excessive colors
Duplicate visuals
Unnecessary gridlines
Prefer:
Consistent spacing
Clear titles
Appropriate chart selection
High data-to-ink ratio

Interactive Features
Enable:
Cross-filtering
Cross-highlighting
Tooltips
Drill-through (Customer, Product, Region)
Sync slicers across pages
Bookmark-based navigation (optional)

Dashboard Validation Checklist
Before publishing:
All visuals load correctly
No blank visuals
Relationships validated
Measures return expected values
Filters work correctly
Drill-through functions correctly
Mobile layout reviewed
Titles are business-friendly
Number formatting is consistent
Currency symbols are correct

Stakeholder Walkthrough
CEO
Overall revenue
Growth trend
Strategic risks
Top opportunities
CFO
Profit
Margin
Discount impact
Revenue trends
COO
Regional operations
Inventory trends
Operational performance
Sales Director
Regional sales
Top customers
Sales trends
Product Manager
Product performance
Category contribution
Loss-making products

Expected Dashboard Outcome
Within five minutes, an executive should be able to answer:
Are we growing?
Are we profitable?
Which products drive revenue?
Which customers are most valuable?
Which regions need attention?
Where should we invest next?

